### 5. Services (`server/app/services/`)

- [ ] **`server/app/services/minio_service.py`** — MinIO operations:
  - `upload(bucket, key, data/file_path)` — upload file or bytes
  - `download(bucket, key)` → bytes
  - `get_presigned_url(bucket, key, expiry=4hrs)` → URL string
  - `list_objects(bucket, prefix)` → list
  - `ensure_buckets()` — create `job-inputs`, `job-outputs`, `checkpoints`, `build-contexts` on startup
  - `get_size(bucket, key)` → int bytes
- [ ] **`server/app/services/redis_service.py`** — Redis operations:
  - `update_heartbeat(node_id, resources_json)` — ZADD to sorted set by timestamp
  - `get_active_nodes(timeout_seconds=30)` → list of active nodes
  - `mark_node_busy(node_id)` / `mark_node_available(node_id)`
  - `push_chunk(chunk_json, priority="normal")` — LPUSH/RPUSH to job queue
  - `pop_chunk()` — RPOP from job queue
  - `publish(channel, message)` — pub/sub for WebSocket broadcasting
  - `subscribe(channel)` — async generator for pub/sub
- [ ] **`server/app/services/notification_service.py`** — WebSocket broadcasting:
  - `broadcast_to_job(job_id, message)` — all clients watching this job
  - `send_to_node(node_id, message)` — specific contributor node
  - `broadcast_to_user(user_id, message)` — all sessions of a user

### 6. WebSocket Manager (`server/app/api/v1/websocket.py`)

- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/websocket.py`** — Connection manager:
  - `ConnectionManager` class with:
    - `active_connections: dict[str, WebSocket]` — node_id → ws
    - `customer_connections: dict[str, list[WebSocket]]` — job_id → [ws clients]
    - `connect_node(node_id, ws)`, `disconnect_node(node_id)`
    - `connect_customer(job_id, ws)`, `disconnect_customer(job_id, ws)`
    - `send_to_node(node_id, data)`, `broadcast_to_job(job_id, data)`
  - WS route `/api/v1/ws/node/{node_id}` — node agent persistent connection
  - WS route `/api/v1/ws/job/{job_id}` — customer live monitoring
  - Heartbeat message handler → calls redis_service.update_heartbeat
  - Job status message handler → updates chunk in DB + broadcasts to customer

### 7. API Endpoints (`server/app/api/v1/`)

- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/router.py`** — Aggregated router including all sub-routers
- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/users.py`** — Auth endpoints:
  - `POST /api/v1/auth/register` — email + password registration
  - `POST /api/v1/auth/login` — returns JWT
  - `POST /api/v1/auth/google` — OAuth exchange code → JWT
  - `GET /api/v1/auth/me` — current user profile
- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/nodes.py`** — Node endpoints:
  - `POST /api/v1/nodes/register` — register contributor machine (specs, returns node_id + cert)
  - `GET /api/v1/nodes/me` — contributor's own node(s) info
  - `GET /api/v1/nodes/stats` — cluster stats (total nodes, available, GPU hours today)
- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/jobs.py`** — Job endpoints:
  - `POST /api/v1/jobs` — multipart file upload → MinIO → create job record → kick pipeline
  - `GET /api/v1/jobs/{job_id}` — job status + chunks
  - `GET /api/v1/jobs` — list user's jobs (paginated)
  - `POST /api/v1/jobs/{job_id}/cancel` — cancel running job
- [ ] **`server/app/api/v1/billing.py`** — Billing endpoints:
  - `GET /api/v1/billing/estimate` — price estimate for given GPU tier + hours
  - `GET /api/v1/billing/earnings` — contributor earnings summary
  - `GET /api/v1/billing/history` — billing records (paginated)

